cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG 

This paper involves natural language processing and computer vision techniques for fashion image retrieval, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on image retrieval and uses visual attributes to train the model. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely, as the paper involves natural language annotations and feedback for the retrieval system. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category, as the paper deals with retrieving images based on user feedback and side information. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a relevant category, as the paper involves both visual and textual modalities for fashion image retrieval. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible, as the paper proposes a novel approach for combining natural language feedback and visual attributes to improve retrieval performance.
